Debouncer delays API call until user stops typing. Without it, every keystroke fires request → hammers server, wastes bandwidth, causes flickering results.

Typical: 250-300ms delay. User types "react hooks" → 11 keystrokes → 1 request instead of 11.

```js
const debouncedSearch = debounce((q) => fetch(`/api?q=${q}`), 300);
input.addEventListener('input', (e) => debouncedSearch(e.target.value));
```

