   ```

3. **No memoization on the child** — React re-renders children by default when a parent renders, even if props haven't changed. Wrap with `React.memo()`:
   ```jsx
   const Child = React.memo(function Child({ name }) {
     return <div>{name}</div>;
   });
   ```
   `React.memo` does a shallow comparison of props — which is why fixes #1 and #2 matter (unstable references defeat the shallow check).

